\"><strong>Fen\u2019Harel Altars</strong> are those wolf statue puzzles you might have seen in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/dragon-age-the-veilguard/440892\">Dragon Age: The Veilguard</a></em>. Though fully optional, it\u2019s worth tracking down as many Fen\u2019Harel Altars as you can: You\u2019ll get an extra skill point for every statue you find.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Thing is, each Fen\u2019Harel Altar requires you to solve a little puzzle before getting its reward. Our <em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em> guide will show you <strong>wh", "id": 1459803, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/474740/fenharel-altars-all-locations-where-to-find-statues-solutions", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "All Fen\u2019Harel Altar locations and solutions in Dragon Age: The Veilguard", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T15:31:11+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25347866/stardew_valley_meadowlands_coop.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Some <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/stardew-valley/38933\">Stardew Valley</a></em> players on console or mobile are having performance issues <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/474195/stardew-valley-1-6-update-console-mobile-switch\">after the 1.6 patch dropped on Monday</a>. Eric \u201cConcernedApe\u201d Barone is advising players to remove all hats from all pets to potentially fix the issue.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">\u201cPSA: if you are experiencing performance issues in Stardew Valley 1.6, remove all hats from pets,\u201d <a href=\"https://x.com/ConcernedApe/status/1853889827294650577\">Barone wrote on X</a>. \u201c", "id": 1459471, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/474852/stardew-valley-no-hats-on-pets-1-6-update", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Stardew Valley broken? Try removing your pets\u2019 hats", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T15:07:26+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Stardew_Valley_2024-11-05_12-26-55.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=17,3.9111111111111,66.6,85.422222222222\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">After maxing out all your skills in <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/guides/22214976/stardew-valley-beginners-tips-tricks\">Stardew Valley</a></em>, you\u2019ll unlock <strong>skill mastery</strong> via the Mastery Cave in the Cindersap Forest. You\u2019ll be able to improve your skills (farming, mining, foraging, fishing, and combat) even further with upgrades and item recipes that\u2019ll help any end-game <em>Stardew</em> player out a ton.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Below, we explain how to unlock the <em>Stardew Valley</em>\u2019s Mastery Cave and skill mastery, what each mastery unlocks, as well as suggestions as to which", "id": 1459472, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/guides/474719/stardew-valley-mastery-cave-skills-best", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to unlock mastery in Stardew Valley", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-left\">Once upon a time, there was a teenage girl, the bastion of innocence, who became enamored with a centuries-old bad boy with an eternal curse. Amid a tumultuous love triangle, quasi-real breakup, and a chapters-long fight over their surprise baby, they battled for their happily-ever-after and captured the hearts of millions of invested fans.</p>\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-vox-media-highlight vox-media-highlight\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"></h2>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/logo_final_digital_f54e00.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,10.732984293194,100,78.534031413613\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" />\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>This week on Polygon, we\u2019re exploring how superheroes are dominating not just comics and movies, but all media, in a special issue called <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/special", "id": 1459081, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/culture/471037/crack-ships-fanfiction", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "When crack ships crack the superhero mainstream", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T13:58:54+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/pokemon-tcg-pocket-dropevent-lapras-extend.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Pok\u00e9mon Trading Card Game Pocket</em> was released on Oct. 30, and already the game\u2019s second in-game event is live. The event \u2014 which appeared on the author\u2019s app around 1 a.m. EST Tuesday and which runs through Nov. 17 \u2014 allows collectors to add a powerful Lapras ex and a handful of other new cards to their digital binders.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Unlike the mobile game\u2019s first event, which is still ongoing and offers a chance at pulling new cards by simply utilizing the Wonder Pick system, <em>Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket</em>\u2019s drop event is all about battling. Taking part in a limited series of solo battles against a CPU opponen", "id": 1459082, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/474735/pokemon-tcg-pocket-battle-event-lapras", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket&#8217;s second in-game event is all about Lapras", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T12:46:58+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25356277/download.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Eric \u201cConcernedApe\u201d Barone announced Tuesday <a href=\"https://x.com/ConcernedApe/status/1853844270807175428\">that he secretly added an \u201cexperimental mobile multiplayer feature\u201d to <em>Stardew Valley</em></a> on mobile. Why is it secret? Barone wrote in a post on the <em>Stardew Valley </em>website that it may have \u201csome bugs or issues,\u201d and that the \u201cnature of the mobile platform could make a multiplayer session frustrating, under certain scenarios.\u201d</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">And Barone wasn\u2019t exaggerating when he said it was hidden. To access it from the mobile version of the game\u2019s title screen, players must perform a sequence", "id": 1458637, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/474732/stardew-valley-1-6-multiplayer-mode-mobile-ios-android", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "\u2018Secret\u2019 multiplayer mode added to Stardew Valley on mobile", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T12:14:20+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: ConcernedApe via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25348196/StardewModdingAPI_2024_03_21_00_46_31.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,93.814432989691\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><strong>Mystery Boxes</strong> are a new type of treasure item found in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/guides/22214976/stardew-valley-beginners-tips-tricks\"><em>Stardew Valley</em></a>\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24106083/stardew-valley-1-6-update-live-2024-patch-notes\">1.6 update</a>. These boxes can be opened to get rewards, but you won\u2019t actually see any Mystery Boxes around the valley until you meet certain unlock criteria.</p>\n\n<p>Below, we describe where to find Mystery Boxes and how to open them in <em>Stardew Valley</em>.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\" />\n\n<", "id": 1458081, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/guides/24107906/stardew-valley-sdv-mystery-box-locations-unlock-open", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where to find Mystery Boxes in Stardew Valley", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T10:14:36+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A woman in a gray space suit standing inside a green pod-like structure in a concept trailer for Scavengers Reign.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Green Street Pictures\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/vlcsnap-2024-11-05-08h42m45s336.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">On Monday, Joseph Bennett, the co-creator of the animated sci-fi drama <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24178625/scavengers-reign-co-creator-joe-bennett-interview-season-2-netflix\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.polygon.com/24178625/scavengers-reign-co-creator-joe-bennett-interview-season-2-netflix\">Scavengers Reign</a></em>, posted an update regarding the series\u2019 status on Instagram. Bad news first: Netflix has passed on the opportunity to greenlight a second season of the Emmy-nominated series. In", "id": 1457355, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/trailer/474654/scavengers-reign-season-2-concept-trailer-announcement", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Scavengers Reign season 2 isn&#8217;t happening yet, but at least we have a new trailer", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"All the companion characters from Dragon Age: The Veilguard sitting around a table together\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: BioWare/Electronic Arts\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/dragon-age-veilguard-companions.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">As is expected from <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/explained/472291/dragon-age-veilguard-lore-explained-beginners-guide\">Dragon Age</a>, there are <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/dragon-age-veilguard-guides/471892/romance-options-all-how-to-romance-characters\">romance options galore</a> in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/470712/review-dragon-age-the-veilguard-ps5-xbox-pc\"><em>Dragon Age: The Veilguard</em></a> \u2014 and the fan discussion on which non-player character to romance began months before the game even came out.&n", "id": 1457356, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/474441/dragon-age-the-veilguard-companion-romances", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How Dragon Age: The Veilguard\u2019s writers decided each companion\u2019s romance arc", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T09:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"Comic panel artworks shows the characters from Sentinels of the Multiverse fighting with each other\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Greater Than Games\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/sentinels.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Greater Than Games founders Christopher Badell, Adam Rebottaro, and Paul Bender first brought up the idea of a new version of their hit cooperative superhero comics card game <em>Sentinels of the Multiverse</em> in a hotel room at PAX West in 2019. The 10th anniversary of the game that started their company in 2011 was approaching, and Rebottaro, who did all the card art, wanted the chance to show off how his style had evolved. A reprint with new artwork seemed simple enough, but writer and designer Badell wanted to revise the flavor text to go with", "id": 1456867, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/tabletop-games/472774/sentinels-of-the-multiverse-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sentinels of the Multiverse might be the best superhero board game \u2014 but its creator wants to do better", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T08:36:05+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"An image of a white Nintendo Switch OLED and a black-and-white controller superimposed on a white background\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/07/Nintendo_Switch_OLED.webp?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Nintendo\u2019s president said there was no change to its plans to announce <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/23899504/nintendo-switch-2-release-date-power-name-games\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/23899504/nintendo-switch-2-release-date-power-name-games\">Switch 2</a> by the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24151013/nintendo-switch-2-direct-announcement-teaser\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.polygon.com/24151013/nintendo-switch-2-direct-announcement-teaser\">end of March 2025</a> as the company reported a sharp decl", "id": 1456868, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/474643/nintendo-switch-2-announcement-no-change", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nintendo has no plans to fast-track Switch 2 announcement as Switch sales fall fast", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/25506945/Elden_Ring_SotE_Bayle_1.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>This story is part of Straight Fire, an open-ended love letter to all things dragon. Get more fire <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/473245\">here</a>.</em></p>\n\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">Fire crackles like lightning from what\u2019s left of Bayle the Dread\u2019s wings \u2014 there\u2019s just gruesome bone where a wing might otherwise be \u2014 flowing like blood behind his armored, scaly body. Not only does Bayle the Dread spit fire from his owl-like beak, the monster <em>is</em> fire incarnate, able to pull from the elements to sprout spectral wings that glow and hiss like flames. Bayle the Dread is the enemy of enemies in", "id": 1456391, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/analysis/471742/elden-ring-video-game-dragons", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "In Elden Ring, dragons are three-dimensional characters", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A skyrim dragon breathing fire in promo art, color graded with yellow and red\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Graphic: Polygon; Source images: Bethesda Softworks\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/skyrimart.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">To quote J.R.R. Tolkein, \u201cI desired dragons with a profound desire.\u201d Who doesn\u2019t, really? Dragons have endured for centuries in fantasy literature, worming their way into the imaginations of readers and writers across cultures. Dragons are, depending on who you ask, wonder and imagination, destruction and awe.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">This is <em>Straight Fire</em>, a column that\u2019ll be published on Polygon twice a month, where I\u2019ll use my expertise to analyze and tell stories about dragon media \u2014 largely video games. What makes a comp", "id": 1456394, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/analysis/473245/straight-fire-dragons-love-letter", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Straight Fire: A love letter to dragons", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24674487/Light_dragon.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>This story is part of Straight Fire, an open-ended love letter to all things dragon. Get more fire <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/473245\">here</a>.</em></p>\n\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">A shimmering, wingless dragon slithers through the sky high above Hyrule. Get close enough to <em>The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom</em>\u2019s Light Dragon \u2014 all golden scales and glowing teal shards \u2014 and you\u2019ll notice something unique about this dragon: the Master Sword is embedded in the dragon\u2019s head, stuck right between its horns. And it\u2019s no accident that Link\u2019s weapon is stuck in this particular dragon\u2019s skull; the Li", "id": 1456392, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/472430/zelda-tears-of-the-kingdom-light-dragon-lore", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Tears of the Kingdom\u2019s Light Dragon can teach you a lot about Zelda\u2019s legacy", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T08:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/12107975/skyrim_remastered.0.0.0.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>This story is part of Straight Fire, an open-ended love letter to all things dragon. Get more fire <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/e/473245\">here</a>.</em></p>\n\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">How do you name a dragon? In <em>The Elder Scrolls 5: Skyrim</em>, a dragon\u2019s name is a representation of its legacy; a name appears to be earned, not simply given, <a href=\"https://skyrimforum.com/forum/threads/how-do-dragons-get-their-names.70231/\">according to some theories</a>. <a href=\"https://bethesda.net/en/article/1rL4bCScN6RYXaXQb4ownj/how-bethesda-game-studios-made-skyrims-dragon-language\">Dragon language</a", "id": 1456393, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/472734/skyrim-dragon-names-rotmulaag-thuum-org", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can use this website to learn the meaning of every Skyrim dragon\u2019s name", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-05T06:57:38+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Microsoft-Flight-Simulator-2024_Limitless_Screenshot_12.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2024/11/04/xbox-game-pass-november-2024-wave-1/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2024/11/04/xbox-game-pass-november-2024-wave-1/\">Xbox Wire</a> has laid out the additions to Game Pass for the first half of November, and the task of keeping the momentum of big day-one releases on the service going after last month\u2019s <em>Call of Duty: Black Ops 6</em> falls to <em>Microsoft Flight Simulator 2024</em>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Polygon recently had a chance to take the 2024 edition of the class-leading aviation sim for a test flight and found it <a href=\"https:", "id": 1456065, "language": null